                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The National Intelligence University,
                                                  formerly the Joint Military Intelligence College,
                                                  was established in 1962. The College is a joint
                                                  service interagency educational institution
                                                  serving the intelligence community and operates
                                                  under the authority of the Director, Defense
                                                  Intelligence Agency. Its mission is to educate
                                                  military and civilian intelligence professionals,
                                                  conduct and disseminate relevant intelligence
                                                  research, and perform academic outreach regarding
                                                  intelligence matters. The College is authorized by
                                                  Congress to award the bachelor of science in
                                                  intelligence, master of science and technology
                                                  intelligence, and master of science of strategic
                                                  intelligence. Courses are offered to full-time
                                                  students in a traditional daytime format and for
                                                  part-time students in the evening, on Saturday,
                                                  and in an executive format (one weekend per month
                                                  and a 2-week intensive summer period).</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                    </Details>
                </Activity>
